PETSc (Portable, Extensible Toolkit for Scientific Computation) is a suite of data structures and routines developed for the scalable solution of scientific problems. It is significant for enabling efficient parallel numerical computations, particularly in solving partial differential equations (PDEs). Below is an example of how PETSc might be used in a simple linear solver:
c
#include <petscksp.h>
int main(int argc, char **args) {
  Vec x, b; Mat A; KSP ksp;
  PetscInitialize(&argc, &args, NULL, NULL);
  VecCreate(PETSC_COMM_WORLD, &x);
  VecCreate(PETSC_COMM_WORLD, &b);
  MatCreate(PETSC_COMM_WORLD, &A);
  // Setup matrix, vector, and solver (omitted for brevity)
  KSPSolve(ksp, b, x);
  PetscFinalize();
  return 0;
}
